Include these tables:
- profiles (extends auth.users with trigger)
- organizations (team workspaces with plan info)
- documents (uploaded files with status tracking)
- extraction_templates (field definitions for doc extraction)
- surveys (survey definitions with questions as JSONB)
- survey_responses (respondent answers)
- analyses (cached AI analysis results)
- api_keys (API key management)
- activity_log (audit trail)

Each table should have:
- UUID primary keys with gen_random_uuid()
- Proper foreign keys with ON DELETE CASCADE
- Timestamps (created_at, updated_at where applicable)
- CHECK constraints for status/enum fields
- Proper indexes

RLS policies:
- All tables: org-based isolation using a helper function is_org_member(org_id)
- survey_responses: public INSERT for active surveys, SELECT only for org members
- profiles: users can read/update own profile

Trigger to auto-create profile on auth.users insert.
Trigger to increment survey response_count on new response.

Storage buckets: 'documents' (private), 'exports' (private).

